==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Egoism
<hw>E"go*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧go⟦ium⟧sme</ets>, fr. L. <ets>-ego</ets> I. See <er>I</er>,
and cf. <er>Egotism</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Philos.)</fld>
<def>The doctrine of certain extreme adherents or disciples of Descartes
and Johann Gottlieb Fichte, which finds all the elements of knowledge in
the <xex>ego</xex> and the relations which it implies or provides
for.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Excessive love and thought of self; the habit of
regarding one's self as the center of every interest; selfishness; --
opposed to <contr>altruism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Egoist</ent>⟦br⟧
